BROWSER JS:

browser js is maninly used for client side or front end applications.
it is sandboxed for the safety purpose and have access limited to the browser
it has all predefined objects but missing on GLOBAL,REQUIRE etc..
it runs in any engine according to the browser.
it is not headless and moduling is not mandatory for browserjs.


NODE JS:

node js is used for backend applications.
it has full system access that is it can read and write directly to the file system.
it has many missing objects like WINDOW,LOCATION,DOCUMENT, etc..
it runs in v8 engine
it is headless that is without any GUI 
in nodejs everything is a module thatis mandatory to keep everything inside a module..
